content: Hi,    I've played music for 50 years. I play by ear. Have produced albums, play multple instruments. I've tried repeatedly to learn to read music. This game provides a fun opportunity.       Thank you,  Harvey McCluskey
Fantastic app. I find this app much less boring and more entertaining than all the others I have tried

Tip: Turn the drum symbol off under settings and the music will stop upon exiting the game. I'm using this for my young children to help them learn their music notes. It's frustrating for them that NO mistakes are allowed on the 2nd star level. Also, much more time needs to be added to the extend time options to accommodate young children. I would suggest at least 10 seconds more. Great app, thanks!  :)
replyContent:
Thanks for your comment :)
The "no mistake" rule is based on learning process in french music schools and was approved by the music teachers I worked with ;) For young children, you can use the +75% extra-time. Example : for an initial timer at 1min, it adds 45s, for 2 min, it adds 1m30s and so on...

content: It helped me know my notes!
Cool game.

Very quick to get into, the vibe of other games it has, makes it relatable and less daunting than other methods of learning music. It makes it simple and encouraging, obviously aimed for kids but if you want to learn to read and play music then this is a very useful tool for any age and can be a fun challenge amongst several people with the same goal.

Extremely hard levels and very tedious progression.   The game forces you to play the same 3 notes per clef about 75 times before giving you 1 more.  Drag that out over 30 levels before you finally get more than 1 octave away from middle c plus I'd you make a single mistake you have to restart the level.  Even 5 year olds get frustrated playing this.
replyContent:
The app's learning process was designed as the meeting of the methods of french music conservatories with the pedagogical progression of learning to read in primary schools. 
It has been tested and approved by several music teachers. 
I'm sorry it doesn't suit to you.
ps : The numbers are lower than those you said ;)

content: Best App! on the market. My new years resolution was and continues to be learning how to play the piano. Talk about teaching an old dog new tricks. Specially when an old dog such as myslef has never played an instrument, nor had any idea what those funny little things on the staff were. After spending countless hours searching online for an actual computer software and apps that make false promises, I came accross Jungle Music. Jungle Music is entertaining and gratifying thus prompting me to share this GATEWAY! to learning the music theory. Initially, this was only my new years resolution but has turned out to now being my entire families new years resolution. Jungle Music's unique attention to details makes this app fun for anyone at any level or age. My wife, both my four and five year old sons are also captivated and we can all enjoy it through the multiplayer option. Allowing me to track everyone's progress which then pushes me to learn more to be able to teach them. I am always looking forward to logging in to start my session finding it hard to stop. I strongly recommend Jungle Music to anyone whether you're a beginner or a more advanced person as you will affectively achieve the desired results while being exhilarated by the different levels and the growth of your character.
replyContent:
Woah ! What a review ! Thank You ! 
Your new years resolution is the good one because Music Makes Life Happier !
